# 1. 恐ろしい知らせ

An: *Sigh* All done for the day!
An: I better get ready to leave so I don't keep Kohane waiting!
Classmate A: Hahaha! An, you always get so happy the second school is out.
Classmate B: You're right. It's like the joy of freedom from the classroom floods her whole being.
An: What do you mean? It's a totally normal reaction, thank you.
An: Anyway, don't you guys have club to get to? The second years won't be happy if you keep dawdling.
Classmate A: Oh my gosh, you're right! See you tomorrow, An!
An: See you! Good luck with club!
An: (Now then...)
An: (It's time for me to get going. What was it again that we're practicing today?)
Mizuki: Hiya, An!
An: Whoa! Mizuki?!
An: C'mon, don't jump out at me like that. What's up?
Mizuki: Hehehe. Do you wanna walk home together today? Someone I know told me about this place with amazing apple pies!
Mizuki: They're supposed to have amazing texture! Soft on the inside and crispy on the outside! Plus, the filling is really sweet, and they're not stingy with it.
An: Wow, that does sound good...
An: But, sorry! I have singing practice with the others today.
Mizuki: Oh, really? Oh well then.
An: Sorry. But thank you for inviting me.
Mizuki: No, you're fine. Let's hang out another—
Teacher: Shiraishi. Akiyama. May I have a word?
An: Yes? What's the matter?
Teacher: There's something we need to discuss. Follow me.
Teacher: Here should be fine.
An: Um, so what is it you need to “discuss”?
Mizuki: Since you took us all the way here... I'm guessing it's something you don't want the whole world hearing?
Teacher: Well, yes... Shiraishi. Do you remember how you did on the tests we had the other day?
An: Huh?
An: I, um... Well... I don't think my grades were high, exactly...
An: B-But, I'm sure they weren't all low! Like, home ec...
Mizuki: Home ec...?
An: Oh yeah! And I didn't fail math either!
Teacher: It's true that you achieved good results for math this time. However... What about classics and chemistry?
An: Um, well... The thing is...
An: A-Anyway! Was there a problem with my test results?
Teacher: Shiraishi... You are a high schooler now.
Teacher: You need to show that you have the academic ability of one to advance to second year.
An: Huh?! Y-You don't mean—
Teacher: Starting Monday, you'll be going to supplementary classes for a week.
An: S-S-Su... Supplementary classes?!
An: B-But, no! You've gotta be kidding!
An: I mean, supplementary classes...
Teacher: I am not kidding! This is no laughing matter.
Teacher: Rules are rules. If you don't score high enough on tests, we have to fail you.
Teacher: That said, we teachers don't want any of you to be held back. We'll be giving you supplementary classes specifically in order to prevent that.
An: *Groan*
Teacher: Now that we're clear on that... I expect you to show up every day on time, starting on Monday.
An: O-Okay...
Mizuki: Ahaha... That sure sucks, An. But, it'll be worth the hard work to make sure you go into second year.
Teacher: What's this Akiyama? It looks like the pot is calling the kettle black.
Mizuki: Huh?
Teacher: You're taking those supplementary classes too.
Mizuki: What?! Wh-Wh-Why?!
Mizuki: But, my test scores were totally fine, weren't they?
Teacher: Yes, I can't deny your academic achievement. The issue is your attendance.
Mizuki: No no no! I did a ton of worksheets the other day 'cause I was told it would make up for my low attendance!
Teacher: Yes, you did. However, you had a string of absences after that.
Mizuki: That's true... But, I made sure they were all days that it would be okay to skip and—
Mizuki: (...? Hang on... Didn't the teacher get sick one time, and math got swapped with English the next day...?)
Mizuki: (Wait. If that's true, then... My English attendance is—)
Teacher: It seems I've jogged your memory?
Mizuki: Uh... Umm... Well... Yes...
Teacher: Well then, have I made myself clear?
Teacher: Shiraishi. Akiyama. I expect you both to attend all of next week's supplementary classes.
An & Mizuki: N-Nooo!
An: ...and, so...
An: I'm sorry, you guys! I have to take supplementary classes all next week!
Kohane: Oh, An...
An: I really am sorry! I've gotta stay back after school every day to study...
An: But, I promise I'll practice as soon as I get home!
Kohane: It can't be helped. Being held back would be terrible...
Toya: Have you talked to your dad yet?
An: Y-Yeah... He told me to knuckle down and study hard so I don't get held back...
Toya: I see...
Toya: Then, there's nothing for me to say. If there's anything I can do to help, let me know.
Rin: Good luck, An!
Rin: I don't really know much about school... But I'll do anything I can to support you!
Len: Me too, me too! I'll make you lots of tasty coffee to keep you energized!
MEIKO: Good idea. I'll make lots of sweet snacks for you too.
An: You guys...
An: Thank you! I'll do my best!
Luka: So, I guess it's just going to be the three of you at practice until An finishes her supplementary classes.
Toya: True. Akito, Azusawa, let's just do what we can for now.
Kohane: *Nod*
Akito: ...
Luka: Akito?
KAITO: Huh? Come to think of it, Akito, you're oddly quiet today. Is something up?
Toya: Akito. Don't tell me...
Akito: ...too.
Miku: What?
Akito: I...have supplementary classes too.
Kohane: Y-You too, Shinonome...?!
Toya: Akito...
An: Hey, why didn't you say so?!
Akito: Sorry...
Len: I-I see... Akito and An, we're rooting for both of you!
Rin: It'd be a disaster if neither of you got to go into second year!
An: Oh... So Akito's taking supplementary classes too...
An: Well, that checks out. It'd be crazy if I had to take supplementary classes but not you...
Akito: Huh?! What's that supposed to mean? I'm smarter than you, and—
An: What? No you're not. I only failed two subjects.
Akito: The same as me, then. And for the record, I scored higher than you in world history.
An: So what? In math, I—
Kohane: B-Both of you, please calm down...
Toya: Yes. Pointlessly arguing over such things changes nothing about the fact that you both failed.
Akito: *Wince*
Toya: The important thing now is for you both to make the most of the supplementary classes.
An: Okay...
Akito: Point taken.
An: (Toya's right...)
An: (These classes are going to be tough, but...)
An: (I've gotta study hard and make sure I get into second year!)
